Valerio Mariani, Cong Wang, SLAC LCLS
* As a data analyst, I would like to stream
data from LCLS detectors to multiple
* Filtering, AI training, and Monte Carlo fit within this pattern
* Framework was used to stream Psana to numpy image array
from SLAC to OLCF at >4 GByte/sec.
* Lower-level optimizations can "invisbly" map operations and
their sequencing to parallel hardware and programming
* tap(fn) call fn on each yielded item
* dup(src2) setup src2 to yield an identical copy of the stream
* tee(context-fn) with a python context, call the fn on each yielded item
* src >> prepend(src2) yield values from src2 then src
* drop(n) read and discard n items
* takei(index list) pass only given indices
* dropi(index list) pass all except these indices
* filter(cond) pass only items matching the condition
* dropwhile(cond) read and discard until cond holds
* apply(fn) call fn(*item) for each item
* map(fn) call fn(item) for each item
* fold(fn, a) call a = fn(a, item) for each item
* chop(n) pass lists of n items
* cut[st:stop:skip] do slice-selection on each item
* pusher push the items to a socket
* maximum(fn) return item with largest fn(item)
* minimum(fn) return item with smallest fn(item)
* last(n) return last items as a list
* append(lst) append all items to lst
* list read entire stream into a list
* fileSink write chunks to a file
* queueSink put the items on a queue
